		<description><![CDATA[Javier Barros del Villar from Mexico City talks about Arte Callejero, his Spanish-language blog.  What started out as a hobby photographing images he saw on the streets of Mexico City, has now become the largest photographic archive of street art in Mexico.
In this podcast, Javier talks about the differences between street art and graffiti [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Javier Barros del Villar from Mexico City talks about <strong><a href="http://arteycallejero.blogspot.com/">Arte Callejero</a></strong>, his Spanish-language blog.  What started out as a hobby photographing images he saw on the streets of Mexico City, has now become the largest photographic archive of street art in Mexico.</p>
<p>In this podcast, Javier talks about the differences between street art and graffiti and also tells us about one work in particular by one of his digital <em>cuates</em> who goes by the clever name <strong><a href="http://aguafiestaz.blogspot.com/">Aguafiestaz</a></strong>. It&#8217;s called <em><strong>me_miras</strong></em>.</p>
<p>This is part 1 of a two-part interview. A transcript will be available later this month.</p>
<p>Javier&#8217;s blog: http://arteycallejero.blogspot.com</p>
