		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://spanish-podcast.com/2007/12/21/vee-011-constitution-day/</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Lydia, my landlady, is back for another conversation about Spanish holidays. In this podcast, Lydia talks about the 6th of December, Spain&#8217;s Constitution Day, and tells us about the ripple effects this historical day has had on Spanish society. Lydia is from Madrid, Spain.
]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Lydia, my landlady, is back for another conversation about Spanish holidays. In this podcast, Lydia talks about the 6th of December, <strong><a href="http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constituci%C3%B3n_espa%C3%B1ola_de_1978">Spain&#8217;s Constitution Day</a></strong>, and tells us about the ripple effects this historical day has had on Spanish society. Lydia is from Madrid, Spain.</p>
<div class="feedflare">
