		<description><![CDATA[Growing up in Distrito Federal (that’s Mexico City), Zuleika Deciga was crazy about radio. She loved listening to radio programs and when she got to college she choose journalism and communications as her major.   After graduation, she spent two-and-a-half years taking voice lessons and acting classes with reknown instructor Tena Curiel in Mexico [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Growing up in Distrito Federal (that’s Mexico City), Zuleika Deciga was crazy about radio. She loved listening to radio programs and when she got to college she choose journalism and communications as her major.   After graduation, she spent two-and-a-half years taking voice lessons and acting classes with reknown instructor Tena Curiel in Mexico City. Zuelika now lives outside of Seattle with her husband and adorable baby girl.</p>
<p>In part one of today’s interview, Zuleika talks about how she followed her dream to enter broadcasting and became that voice on the radio. Part 2 of the interview will be podcast on Wednesday, November 21.</p>
