			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Luis Clemens, a Cuban American and editor of <strong><a href="http://www.lapolitica.com">La Política</a></strong>, introduces us to this new publication about Hispanic voters in the U.S. In this podcast, he talks about the reasons why 2007 is a good year to launch such a specialized publication and politlcal blog. He also discusses what he found when he visited the Spanish web sites of the 2008 U.S. presidential candidates and gives an opinion about why candidates like U.S. Senator John McCain and former New York City mayor Rudolph Guiliani don&#8217;t have campaign web sites in Spanish.</p>
